Monitoring

Target IP: 192.168.246.136

Scanning


There are multiple TCP ports open on the target machine. I will start my enumeration with the HTTP application on port 80.

Enumeration

Port 80: HTTP


We are presented the webpage above when we visit this port from a web-browser.


After some manual enumeration, I did not find anything useful. I found a file called suggest.php and tested it for LFI, but that did not provide anything useful either. After trying to bruteforce the login page using different credentials I had no luck.


Until I found the webpage above. Apparently, nagiosadmin:admin is the default credentials. After spraying this, I got a hit!


The version of the application is mentioned which is 5.6.0.


Apparently this version of application is vulnerable to authenticated RCE. Now we have the credentials, we can launch the attack.

Exploitation


Another version of the exploit exists. I used this linux/http/nagios_xi_plugins_check_plugin_authenticated_rce exploit instead of the one above.


This exploit gave me a root shell right away!

Flags


The proof.txt flag once I gained a root shell after using the exploit.
